The electronic components in the CompM4 include Aimpoint's Super ACET diode circuitry, allowing the sight to run constantly for up to 8 years on a single AA battery. All CompM4 sights feature an internal voltage regulator that allows the sights to operate on any AA size battery available worldwide. These sights also feature a 2 minute-of-angle (MOA) dot size, making them perfectly suited for use with Aimpoint's 3XMagnifier and Concealed Engagement Unit (CEU).
The CompM4 is optimized for use with all generations of night vision devices, and features an extremely rugged and easy to use 16-position manual switch with 7 night vision compatible settings and 9 daylight settings. The CompM4 sight body is designed to protect the optical and electronic components inside against hard use, and keeps the sight waterproof to 45 meters (150
feet).

Features:

- Compatible with every generation of Night Vision Devices (NVD) 
- Super ACET technology allows up to 80,000 hours (over 8 years) of daytime operation on one AA battery 
- Internal voltage regulator allows the CompM4 to be used with any AA size battery.
- Seven night vision compatible settings and 9 daylight settings
- QRP2 mount has twice the clamping force of the original QRP, and the mounting knob is wider and shorter to improve operation, and lessen the chance of becoming snagged on other gear.
- Mount base is “keyed” into to the body of the sight to absorb recoil.
- Mount base screws directly into the sight – no separate sight ring is required.
- 500,000 hours of use on NVD setting 
- 2 MOA dot for close combat and long distance engagement
- Matches perfectly with Aimpoint 3XMag, (magnifier module).
- Unequalled light transmission.
- Front lens opening is threaded for addition of killFlash anti-reflective device.
- Submersible to 150 feet (45 meters) 
- Vertical spacer included
- Standardized as the US Army's new M68CCO 
- Improved adjustment caps are easier to remove, and are protected against impact.
- Can be used with a carry handle adaptor for use on all M16 rifles.

postcontent: Once again I am dropping the price of a gun that has a lot into it. I have sold a few guns and this is the last of the ones I have that does not get carried enough anymore. I am looking at the adds with people asking 650 for a 23 gen 3. Come on folks that is 150 higher than factory. My gun is priced higher because it has something more to offer with the crimson trace laser grip and tritium sights that glow bright as the day they got dialed in. Perfect carry for most anyone and 13 rounds of 40 in a compact is a solid amount, I rarely ever carry the other mag when I take this with me. Gun is clean and the only wear is on the slide release. you have to look close to see even that. Has never failed and with a glock it prob never will unless you are using handmade loads that are not up to par. I have yet to have a malfunction of any kind and for a while I shot this gun every time I went to the range so with a few hundred rounds down the pipe I know I can rely on it.

We have a new baby and need to expand our house, so I'm putting part of my collection up for sale for a down payment on the work.  All items are brand new except two of the scopes.  Not “new with only 100 rounds through it,” or any of the other excuses people are using, but completely unused and ready for you to break in, modify, or register as you wish.  Many components are still in their unopened packaging and have the warranty paperwork where applicable.

Do Not Ask:
If this is available – if you see this ad, this is still for sale

Also includes a Magpul verticle foregrip (not installed) that attaches to the hand guard.  Base model (without Magpul extras) is around $1,000 from dealers
All rifles come with manuals, paperwork, locks, and whatever other accessories normally come with them (i.e. sling and rail risers for Bushmaster, etc).

The Accessories:
- Black Midway USA padded zippered rifle bag with room for 4 30-round mags, a velcro pocket, and a zippered pocket on the outside.  Has a carry handle and shoulder strap on the back.
- Green NCStar padded zippered rifle bag with outside pockets for 4 30-round mags covered by a velcro flap.  Has a carry handle on the side and a shoulder strap on the other.
- 4 Tapco 30-round magazines for the AR-15's
- CAA 30-round magazine
- CAA triple rail system to mount to standard AR 15 hand guard
- Laser/flashlight combination with rail mounting system and remote pressure switches.  Flashlight has a red flip-cap filter to preserve night vision.
- BSA red dot sight scope with built-in sun shade (42 mm)
- UTG CQB reticle intensified red/green dot scope sight (30 mm) (used once on one of my other rifles, but comes with battery, soft case, tool, etc)

- 2 stacking 45 MTM ammo cans with rubber gaskets
- 2 M-16 bayonet's with leather sheathes

The Ammo (only available with purchase of a rifle!!!!):
- 600 rounds of Independence 5.56 ammunition
- 500 rounds of American Eagle AR .223 ammunition
- 60 rounds of Tulammo .223 ammunition


Everything is new except for the UTG and Weaver scopes.  If you buy the whole package I'll include a package of 20 zombie targets for free.  I prefer to sell the collection as one lot, or split the rifles up into packages, but I'm open to selling some of the stuff off individually (i.e. the extra mags as a lot, or a rifle and ammo).

I'm not looking to gouge anyone, but I am looking to get out near what this is all worth.
